for we were far too interested in our own quiet little game of Pontoon to have ant inclination for the rotten wine, in the end the troops shook hands returned to their several quarters enjoyed a good nights repose, after such a strenuous trying evening.
During the afternoon I had a fly at the "two up" School eventually pulled out winning 250 francs which I lost the same night at "pontoon", so much for gambling, but we don't get much money we do see some life, what;
11th. Slept in till 8.30 for during the night we had been warned that we would be moving off today nearly certain for the North again for rumour hath it that the "Pork beans" had put up a most gallant heroic retreat, were
